rlm-git-squash-branch

Squash every commit on the current branch since it diverged from
origin's default branch into a single signed-off commit.

Determines the default branch from
`git symbolic-ref --short refs/remotes/origin/HEAD` (e.g. `origin/main`),
finds the merge base with `git merge-base --fork-point` (falling back to
plain `git merge-base` when fork-point cannot be determined — common on
shallow clones or after a forced upstream rebase), then runs
`git reset --soft <merge-base>` followed by `git commit -s` so the user
can author one combined commit message in their editor.

Refuses to run when:
  - the current HEAD is detached,
  - the current branch is the default branch itself,
  - HEAD is already at the merge base (nothing to squash).

After the squash succeeds, prints the command needed to publish the
rewritten branch:

    git push --force-with-lease

`--force-with-lease` is used rather than `--force` so the push aborts
if someone else pushed to the same branch in the meantime.

REQUIRES
  git
